1
00:00:04,293 --> 00:00:05,993
What are you doing here?

2
00:00:06,813 --> 00:00:09,513
What? Why are you taking a picture?

3
00:00:09,513 --> 00:00:11,546
Why aren't you coming to school?

4
00:00:16,546 --> 00:00:18,846
What's the point of going
to a place like that?

5
00:00:19,813 --> 00:00:21,880
You should at least graduate.

6
00:00:25,446 --> 00:00:27,446
Is school over for today?

7
00:00:28,413 --> 00:00:29,413
No.

8
00:00:29,413 --> 00:00:30,913
Then what are you doing here?

9
00:00:30,913 --> 00:00:33,846
What's the point of going
to a place like that?

10
00:00:33,846 --> 00:00:35,580
You idiot.

11
00:00:40,446 --> 00:00:44,546
Did you say your goodbyes to your dad?

12
00:00:46,380 --> 00:00:48,113
Yeah.

13
00:00:49,713 --> 00:00:52,380
Sorry I couldn't be there.

14
00:00:52,380 --> 00:00:54,080
It's fine.

15
00:00:56,213 --> 00:00:59,680
I wanted to send him off quietly,
so I ended it early.

16
00:00:59,680 --> 00:01:02,480
To be honest, it still doesn't feel real.

17
00:01:02,480 --> 00:01:04,680
I've been in a daze all day.

18
00:01:08,046 --> 00:01:10,313
Well, then...

19
00:01:10,313 --> 00:01:13,180
Come out of your house by 8 am tomorrow.

20
00:01:14,046 --> 00:01:15,046
Why?

21
00:01:15,046 --> 00:01:16,513
So that we can go to school.

22
00:01:16,513 --> 00:01:19,146
If you don't, I'll drag you out myself.

23
00:01:19,146 --> 00:01:21,146
What are you, my teacher?

24
00:01:21,146 --> 00:01:23,246
How about we take a picture?

25
00:01:26,380 --> 00:01:28,113
Here.

26
00:01:29,352 --> 00:01:32,406
- Come on, smile.
- Jeez.

27
00:01:32,406 --> 00:01:33,713
I'm taking it.

28
00:01:33,713 --> 00:01:36,980
One, two, three!

29
00:02:23,046 --> 00:02:26,613
Tae Jeong, you can't tell anyone
what I'm about to tell you.

30
00:02:27,913 --> 00:02:29,980
You know the mayor, Seong Chang Geun?

31
00:02:29,980 --> 00:02:35,546
I... I have evidence that could end
his political career, you know?

32
00:02:35,546 --> 00:02:36,980
It's on my phone.

33
00:02:36,980 --> 00:02:40,913
I tried to report it to the news,
but I got locked up here.

34
00:02:42,220 --> 00:02:45,780
Instead of finding the key,
let's report it first.

35
00:02:45,780 --> 00:02:48,210
- I'll tell Violent Crimes Unit.
- No, you can't.

36
00:02:48,210 --> 00:02:49,251
Why not?

37
00:02:49,251 --> 00:02:51,880
I think the cops are on their side too.

38
00:02:51,880 --> 00:02:54,046
Then I'll tell Chul Jin.

39
00:02:54,046 --> 00:02:55,413
- I'll tell him...
- No.

40
00:02:55,413 --> 00:03:00,146
I can't trust anyone from Dongcheon police.

41
00:03:00,146 --> 00:03:03,480
Tae Jeong, please, I'm begging you.

42
00:03:03,480 --> 00:03:06,546
You're the only one I can trust, okay?

43
00:03:12,113 --> 00:03:14,880
Did you find the key?

44
00:03:16,646 --> 00:03:18,813
What are you doing? Hurry up and open it.

45
00:03:18,813 --> 00:03:21,280
Before that, promise me one thing.

46
00:03:21,280 --> 00:03:22,980
What?

47
00:03:23,746 --> 00:03:26,046
When I open this cage,

48
00:03:27,313 --> 00:03:29,780
run out of the house.

49
00:03:30,580 --> 00:03:32,580
Why?

50
00:03:32,580 --> 00:03:35,513
Because that man is still inside the house.

51
00:03:38,146 --> 00:03:39,880
Promise me.

52
00:03:43,680 --> 00:03:46,446
Okay, fine.

53
00:04:05,013 --> 00:04:06,813
Are you okay?

54
00:04:06,813 --> 00:04:08,546
Yeah.

55
00:04:23,980 --> 00:04:25,713
Thanks.

56
00:04:40,246 --> 00:04:41,946
What are you doing?

57
00:04:43,613 --> 00:04:45,746
What are you doing, I said?

58
00:04:46,446 --> 00:04:48,180
So he's still upstairs?

59
00:04:48,180 --> 00:04:49,846
Don't do it.

60
00:04:49,846 --> 00:04:52,013
You want me to walk away after all this?

61
00:04:52,013 --> 00:04:53,180
You promised.

62
00:04:53,180 --> 00:04:55,513
That punk tried to smash my head in.

63
00:04:55,513 --> 00:05:00,746
If I don't kill him now, I'll die.

64
00:05:43,346 --> 00:05:46,480
How's it in there? Huh? Pretty crappy, right?

65
00:05:46,480 --> 00:05:48,246
Stop it.

66
00:05:48,246 --> 00:05:51,213
Stay out of it.
This has nothing to do with you.

67
00:05:51,213 --> 00:05:55,246
The basement suits you perfectly,
probably because you do dirty work.

68
00:05:55,246 --> 00:05:57,646
There's no need to go this far.

69
00:05:59,713 --> 00:06:04,813
Seems this punk can't read the room.

70
00:06:04,813 --> 00:06:08,080
You're not getting out of here alive, got it?

71
00:06:09,613 --> 00:06:12,780
No, hang on.

72
00:06:12,780 --> 00:06:15,113
It's no fun if you die so easily, right?

73
00:06:15,113 --> 00:06:17,246
You son of a gun.

74
00:06:18,546 --> 00:06:22,180
I went through crap
for days in here, you know?

75
00:06:22,180 --> 00:06:24,980
- Look forward to it.
- Dong Hwa.

76
00:06:24,980 --> 00:06:28,380
Chu Tae Jeong, come upstairs.

77
00:06:41,413 --> 00:06:45,680
I didn't know Dong Hwa would go this far.

78
00:06:53,280 --> 00:06:55,046
I'm sorry.

79
00:07:16,846 --> 00:07:20,213
- What are you doing?
- Come on.

80
00:07:20,213 --> 00:07:23,921
Oh, darn it.

81
00:07:26,280 --> 00:07:28,380
What's all this money?

82
00:07:32,846 --> 00:07:34,546
My phone.

83
00:07:39,413 --> 00:07:42,613
Darn it, this son of a gun.

84
00:08:11,441 --> 00:08:13,585
Come on.

85
00:08:14,980 --> 00:08:18,146
Come on, you gotta be kidding me.

86
00:08:27,680 --> 00:08:29,513
Where's the phone?

87
00:08:30,546 --> 00:08:33,246
Dude, just say it.

88
00:08:34,580 --> 00:08:38,080
You're really trying
to get yourself killed, huh?

89
00:08:38,080 --> 00:08:40,113
There's something you need to know.

90
00:08:40,113 --> 00:08:41,946
There's another killer on the way.

91
00:08:41,946 --> 00:08:43,546
He's going to kill both of you.

92
00:08:43,546 --> 00:08:45,280
Don't change the subject.

93
00:08:46,313 --> 00:08:49,713
Let me go.
That's the only way you'll survive too.

94
00:08:50,780 --> 00:08:53,913
Why should I believe you?

95
00:08:53,913 --> 00:08:56,980
- There's no time.
- Then tell me where the phone is!

96
00:08:56,980 --> 00:08:59,480
- I will if you let me go.
- Do I look stupid?

97
00:08:59,480 --> 00:09:02,313
You'd kill me if I let you go.

98
00:09:02,313 --> 00:09:03,846
No, but the other guy will!

99
00:09:03,846 --> 00:09:05,280
Tell me where the phone is.

100
00:09:05,280 --> 00:09:07,646
We can grab the phone
and leave with Tae Jeong.

101
00:09:07,646 --> 00:09:11,377
That way, we both get to live,
right? Darn it!

102
00:09:15,813 --> 00:09:17,513
Wait.

103
00:09:18,946 --> 00:09:23,313
You... You don't want Chu Tae Jeong to die.

104
00:09:33,413 --> 00:09:35,513
I especially like your ocean drawings.

105
00:09:35,513 --> 00:09:37,813
Where is it?

106
00:09:37,813 --> 00:09:39,413
Faroe Islands.

107
00:09:39,413 --> 00:09:41,780
I'll buy that drawing from you.

108
00:09:41,780 --> 00:09:43,746
Before its value goes up.

109
00:09:53,980 --> 00:09:55,813
Where's the phone?

110
00:09:55,813 --> 00:10:00,046
If you tell me, I'll spare Tae Jeong.

111
00:10:04,313 --> 00:10:06,013
The phone...

112
00:10:07,913 --> 00:10:10,213
It's in my art supply box.

113
00:10:10,213 --> 00:10:12,746
Took you long enough.

114
00:10:12,746 --> 00:10:14,546
Keep your word.

115
00:10:15,413 --> 00:10:19,113
Please. Chu Tae Jeong has to come with us.

116
00:10:50,980 --> 00:10:53,180
Ah, darn it!

117
00:10:55,146 --> 00:10:57,880
It's not here, that lying crook.

118
00:10:57,880 --> 00:11:02,413
Hey, did you touch anything here?

119
00:11:02,413 --> 00:11:04,146
No.

120
00:11:07,080 --> 00:11:09,313
He's really pissing me off to the end.

121
00:11:17,546 --> 00:11:19,813
Why are you going that far?

122
00:11:19,813 --> 00:11:22,913
Don't worry, I'm not going to kill him yet.

123
00:11:22,913 --> 00:11:26,746
If I cut off his fingers one by one,
he'll tell me where it really is.

124
00:11:32,580 --> 00:11:36,346
Are you really the Heo Dong Hwa I know? Huh?

125
00:11:36,346 --> 00:11:38,713
Tae Jeong.

126
00:11:38,713 --> 00:11:41,246
You need to get out of my house now.

127
00:11:45,480 --> 00:11:47,280
The phone.

128
00:11:50,246 --> 00:11:52,980
You said it has evidence
of the mayor's corruption.

129
00:11:54,146 --> 00:11:56,580
Then you can just report it.

130
00:11:58,180 --> 00:12:01,346
Why on earth are you trying to hurt someone?

131
00:12:01,346 --> 00:12:03,680
Get out of here right now.

132
00:12:04,313 --> 00:12:06,680
Tell me more about that evidence.

133
00:12:07,480 --> 00:12:10,880
Because I need to know
why you're going this far.

134
00:12:10,880 --> 00:12:13,580
If you hurt that guy,

135
00:12:14,913 --> 00:12:17,580
I'll report it, even if it's you.

136
00:12:19,013 --> 00:12:20,746
Tae Jeong.

137
00:12:21,513 --> 00:12:23,780
I almost got killed by that guy.

138
00:12:23,780 --> 00:12:27,713
I was locked up, living like an animal,
and barely made it out alive.

139
00:12:30,680 --> 00:12:33,346
And you're going to report me?

140
00:12:33,346 --> 00:12:35,613
Whose side are you on?

141
00:12:39,180 --> 00:12:40,980
What was that?

142
00:12:40,980 --> 00:12:42,946
Darn it.

143
00:14:22,413 --> 00:14:25,146
Yes, it seems no one's here.

144
00:14:26,946 --> 00:14:29,246
Looks like they already ran off.

145
00:14:33,480 --> 00:14:36,446
I wanted to stab them myself
since it's been a while.

146
00:14:36,446 --> 00:14:38,513
It's a shame.

147
00:14:38,513 --> 00:14:42,013
Seems like that punk left with the cop.

148
00:14:42,013 --> 00:14:44,846
Should I first take care of
Heo Dong Hwa in the basement?

149
00:14:45,713 --> 00:14:47,446
Yes.

150
00:14:49,113 --> 00:14:50,880
Then I'll finish him quickly

151
00:14:50,880 --> 00:14:53,913
and go after the two who ran off.

152
00:14:53,913 --> 00:14:57,446
Once we secure the phone,
I can kill them all, right?

153
00:15:29,013 --> 00:15:30,913
Didn't think you'd die like this, huh?

154
00:15:30,913 --> 00:15:35,313
Take a good look. This is the last thing
you'll see, you crackhead.

155
00:15:45,680 --> 00:15:46,746
Dong Hwa.

156
00:15:46,746 --> 00:15:48,480
Tae Jeong.

157
00:15:55,246 --> 00:15:57,513
Ah, these cockroaches.

158
00:15:57,513 --> 00:15:58,780
Why aren't you dead?

159
00:15:58,780 --> 00:15:59,780
Tae Jeong.

160
00:15:59,780 --> 00:16:02,013
What's going on?

161
00:16:02,013 --> 00:16:03,346
You clueless idiot.

162
00:16:03,346 --> 00:16:06,680
You don't need to know,
since you're going to die anyway.

163
00:16:06,680 --> 00:16:09,113
Dong Hwa, don't shoot.

164
00:16:09,113 --> 00:16:10,280
You can't kill people.

165
00:16:10,280 --> 00:16:13,280
Yeah, listen to your friend.

166
00:16:13,280 --> 00:16:15,346
You piece of crap!

167
00:16:15,346 --> 00:16:18,080
Lower your body a bit more
and push your hips back.

168
00:16:18,080 --> 00:16:20,013
Now try again.

169
00:16:24,113 --> 00:16:25,846
No.

170
00:16:30,846 --> 00:16:32,646
Heo Dong Hwa.

171
00:16:36,746 --> 00:16:38,446
Where are you going?

172
00:16:41,280 --> 00:16:43,946
I gotta kill that punk downstairs too.

173
00:16:43,946 --> 00:16:45,680
Why?

174
00:16:45,680 --> 00:16:47,456
Darn it!

175
00:16:48,580 --> 00:16:51,780
Why? Why?

176
00:16:51,780 --> 00:16:56,180
Are you... Are you stupid
or just pretending to be?

177
00:16:56,180 --> 00:16:58,980
Drop the nice guy act now.

178
00:17:08,613 --> 00:17:10,313
What about Tae Jeong?

179
00:17:11,046 --> 00:17:13,113
Chu Tae Jeong is okay, right?

180
00:17:15,180 --> 00:17:18,380
Wow, seriously, I'm about to tear up.

181
00:17:18,380 --> 00:17:19,780
What are you two?

182
00:17:19,780 --> 00:17:22,646
Did you play house while I was gone?

183
00:17:22,646 --> 00:17:24,346
This is your last chance.

184
00:17:24,346 --> 00:17:27,113
Tell me where the phone is.

185
00:17:28,646 --> 00:17:31,346
You promised to let him go safely.

186
00:17:33,280 --> 00:17:35,280
I'm so done with you.

187
00:17:35,280 --> 00:17:38,513
Forget it. I'll just find it myself.

188
00:17:40,213 --> 00:17:42,080
See you in hell.

189
00:17:43,113 --> 00:17:44,846
The phone!

190
00:17:49,913 --> 00:17:51,680
I have it.

191
00:17:53,313 --> 00:17:55,713
Are you kidding me right now?

192
00:17:55,713 --> 00:17:57,013
Give it to me.

193
00:17:57,013 --> 00:17:58,746
Before that,

194
00:17:59,846 --> 00:18:04,013
- I have something to ask you.
- You've been pushing your luck.

195
00:18:04,013 --> 00:18:05,646
Stop it, or you'll regret it.

196
00:18:05,646 --> 00:18:07,346
Tae Jeong.

197
00:18:10,913 --> 00:18:12,746
My father's belongings.

198
00:18:14,946 --> 00:18:16,780
This notebook.

199
00:18:21,913 --> 00:18:23,780
Why is it in this house?

200
00:18:23,780 --> 00:18:27,613
Why are you all so eager to kill my friend?

201
00:18:28,680 --> 00:18:30,713
Stupid moron.

202
00:18:30,713 --> 00:18:33,346
Can't believe you're friends
with Heo Dong Hwa.

203
00:18:34,913 --> 00:18:36,546
Chu Dae Seok...

204
00:18:36,546 --> 00:18:40,813
Your father wouldn't have died
if it weren't for Heo Dong Hwa.

205
00:18:41,913 --> 00:18:43,813
You know my dad?

206
00:18:45,613 --> 00:18:47,880
Go to the study.

207
00:18:47,880 --> 00:18:50,613
There'll be something familiar.

208
00:18:51,846 --> 00:18:54,846
What's that? I don't know anything about it.

209
00:18:58,480 --> 00:19:01,013
This is my dad's signature.

210
00:19:01,013 --> 00:19:03,080
Didn't you know?

211
00:19:03,080 --> 00:19:08,213
I heard that if not for you,
my dad wouldn't have passed away.

212
00:19:08,213 --> 00:19:10,713
- What does that mean?
- Tae Jeong, calm down.

213
00:19:10,713 --> 00:19:12,713
How is your father's death my fault?

214
00:19:12,713 --> 00:19:15,680
Who said that? Did that punk upstairs say so?

215
00:19:18,413 --> 00:19:20,646
Tell me the truth.

216
00:19:20,646 --> 00:19:23,146
I feel like an idiot for thinking of you

217
00:19:23,146 --> 00:19:26,346
- as my friend.
- I said nothing happened.

218
00:19:27,280 --> 00:19:29,213
Don't come any closer.

219
00:19:29,213 --> 00:19:31,280
I said don't move!

220
00:19:33,013 --> 00:19:34,746
Shoot me.

221
00:19:35,580 --> 00:19:36,946
If you can.

222
00:19:36,946 --> 00:19:39,180
- Tae Jeong.
- What is wrong with you?

223
00:19:39,180 --> 00:19:41,380
Tell me.

224
00:19:41,380 --> 00:19:43,680
What did you do to my father?

225
00:19:45,521 --> 00:19:47,980
- Tae Jeong.
- Tell me now!

226
00:19:49,746 --> 00:19:51,980
Because I know everything.

227
00:19:55,380 --> 00:19:57,146
Isn't it obvious?

228
00:19:57,846 --> 00:20:00,913
It's because your father died here.

229
00:20:05,413 --> 00:20:07,180
Tae Jeong!

